  <h2 id="overview" class="vf-u-margin--0 vf-u-padding__top--400 vf-u-padding__bottom--600 vf-search-client-side--no-index">Overview</h2>
  <p>Sustaining Low Resource Optimisation requires embedding it into long-term planning, delivery practices, and team priorities. Quick wins are useful, but LRO only lasts when it is part of roadmaps, funding decisions, and governance.</p>

  <h2 id="sustainable-adoption" class="vf-u-margin--0 vf-u-padding__top--400">Sustainable LRO adoption</h2>
  <p>LRO should be treated as an ongoing practice rather than a one-off programme.</p>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Embed LRO checks into design, development, and release cycles</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Align LRO with accessibility, performance, and sustainability goals</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Prevent regressions through regular review and accountability</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="roadmap-integration" class="vf-u-margin--0 vf-u-padding__top--400">Roadmap integration</h2>
  <p>LRO should be visible in product and technical roadmaps at all planning horizons.</p>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Define short-, medium-, and long-term LRO goals</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Prioritise high-impact optimisation alongside feature delivery</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Ensure new work does not introduce performance or accessibility regressions</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Move from isolated fixes to platform-level optimisation patterns</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="resourcing" class="vf-u-margin--0 vf-u-padding__top--400">Sustainability and resourcing</h2>
  <p>Clear ownership and recurring investment are essential for durable LRO outcomes.</p>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Define whether ownership is distributed across teams or supported by a central function</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Allocate ongoing resourcing for maintenance and improvement</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Include LRO explicitly in funding and delivery planning</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="measurement" class="vf-u-margin--0 vf-u-padding__top--400">Measurement and continuous improvement</h2>
  <p>Sustainable adoption requires measurable outcomes and regular review.</p>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Define and enforce performance budgets (for example page weight and JavaScript size)</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Track key indicators such as FCP, TBT, and data usage</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Monitor real-user performance across regions and device types</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Run regular audits to detect regressions and prioritise improvements</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="cross-team" class="vf-u-margin--0 vf-u-padding__top--400">Cross-team alignment</h2>
  <p>LRO is a shared responsibility across design, engineering, product, and leadership.</p>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Designers prioritise content-first and lightweight interface decisions</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Developers implement efficient rendering and resource delivery strategies</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Product owners include LRO criteria in planning and acceptance</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Leadership provides governance, prioritisation, and sustained support</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="long-term" class="vf-u-margin--0 vf-u-padding__top--400">Long-term vision</h2>
  <p>Over time, LRO should become a default principle rather than a specialist activity.</p>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Lightweight and resilient design becomes standard practice</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Performance and accessibility are embedded in platforms and design systems</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Teams proactively design for constrained environments from the start</li>
  </ul>
